The paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for the classification of breast carcinomas in whole slide histopathology images. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for image analysis, which is a common theme in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
